<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> on my oath • on oath</xh5><p> <i>on my oath</i>—is said to emphasize that one is telling the truth: I didn’t say anything to him about you, <u>on my oath</u>.</p><p> <i>on oath</i>—(legal) having sworn to tell the truth <i>(also: under oath):</i> The judge reminded the witness that he was still <u>on oath</u>.</p> </entry>
